Amaaaazinnggg. Dark in color beautiful noose nice and creamy please try it its deff worth the momey
Soooo gooood! Nice vanilla notes, Bourbon is straight up on the palate all day long! The brewery is awesome
beer_name: Griffin Claw Flying Buffalo Imperial Stout

review_blob: Bourbon, Bacon syrup, Maple this was one of my favorite back stage series beer Ive ever had! Its so smooth be careful when you drink this one its a big beer! Delcious!
Very good DIPA, Pours a redish color, Really hoppy, Nice piney flavors danky for sure, Try one!
beer_name: Bells Planet Series: Mars - The Bringer Of War

review_blob: West coast style for sure, Piney citrus bitter, Its a really good dipa, Almost better then hopslam-

Wasnt like anything I was expecting as this beer is there flag ship brew, piney floral notes kinda sticky/choppy, not bad for a pale ale, Love the bitter notes that stick around on the tongue but wasnt what I was expecting. Not bad..
This is my go to beer and a hot day the flavors are just right its not heavy and it goes down great! Try the new cans way better then the bottles no light hits the can at all! Must try!
When I was a young lad this was great stuff. but times have changed you cant pay me enough to taste this again..
Its just decent by no means would I go out of My way to purchase this, But this is one of my favorite brewerys! Kinda choppy citrus flavors are a overabundance mellow

Wow.. I was so hyped up and ready to try this "Famous" stout.. wrong right from the pallet I had a HUGE malty/ Watery taste. Aroma wasnt even nice. Maybe I got a bad batch Im not sure I usually dont give bad rates but wow...

Soooooooooooo good! Floral/grapefruit notes I could literally drink 20 of these! A great beer for a hot day! Very hard to get unless you live in the area! Absolutely try it if you can get it!- You will be doing youre self a favor\flavor.!

Smooth nice notes of coffee/roasty! Creamy just a well balanced stout the taste will blow your pallet right out of your mouth chocolate coffe vanilla some dark fruit notes! Do your self a favor and try it!

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: The nose didnt really pick up much of anything but taste wasnt horrible I would much rater drink this then your millers/Buds/coors. Fruit\malt/dry.
"Its so hot" kinda beer very dual not much of any thing. But if you like are light lager then this is you.
Just a amazingly well put together beer! Notes of chocolate roast malts vanilla I could drink this everyday! A+
If the saying is true "Bottom of the barrel" then this is it, Piss color, taste of aluminum just a gross beer.
Amazing! Bitter sweet fruits mango peaches with plenty enough hops! Just a fantastic IPA!
Good beer for someone trying to get out of the buds coors millers. Skunky due to its bottle but a nice crafted beer!

I dont give 5 to often but this has to be a 5 for me anyways! Just enough hops with a really nice sweet bitter taste I would almost call this a session ale because you do not taste the alcohol! Fruits/hops/bitter! Love it! Cans are so nice to have! Makes it easy to smuggle in on the golf course! Haha!
Scotch immediatley hits youre pallet! Dark fruit some good notes of smokey flavors! If your a fan of scotch ales then this is all you! Wasnt to impressed! Little strong with the scotch!

Hops Hops Hops! Beautiful beer a very big beer! The fruits the aroma all hit your pallet at once and makes it just so nice! If youre a hop head then this is all you! For a double this is bar none one of my Favorite! They only brew it once a year so pick it up!

I have nothing wrong to say about this beautiful crafted beer! Smokey bourbon flavors coffe dark fruits! Its the best stout I think Ive ever had! Its a real big beer bought two bottles going to cellar the other for a good year our so it will only get better! Its really hard to find but if you can find it PICK IT UP!

This is a wonderful summer lager! Aroma is beautiful taste is phenomenal gives about a little under a finger of head! Fruits pears with just enough hops to make it really refreshing! Its definitely a summer brew makes it great for mowing the lawn! Cheers!
The best beer to be found in my opinion at the brewery Besides Twisted Helles. I like the flavor and its not too dark to be enjoyed while eating the food offered at the brewery.

This brewery is amazing dont get me wrong! First time having there stout wasnt very impressive, The taste was very daul with a water down finish the Coffe/Roasty Aroma! The reason why I think I even finished it was because you could taste the Hops! Very depressing!
Wasnt the best pale ale this is a good trans beer for someone trying to get in the habbit of drinking good beer taste wasnt to bad I feel as if this beer has a lot more potential then it has!
Was very excited to try this beer! But the flavor was daul kinda upsetting giving the hype if this beer!
beer_name: Big Sky Moose Drool Brown Ale

review_blob: I absolutely love this place! The environment is so friendly and you feel very welcomed! Now onto the beer this beer has been one of the best beer I have ever had in my life! The smoothest the flavors all hit youre pallet at once and makes one beautiful crafted beer if you are ever in the area come stop by!
Color was nice, taste wasnt what I was expecting kinda choppy to be honest kinda dual but it is made by bells so I wont complain much more then that.
This is a wonderful beer for any Hop lover, Great thing about it is you can have more then a "few" and still function. Not to mention the cans are great for the golf course!
